This was meant for compatibility with `langchain-openai`'s convention to store reasoning text in the `reasoning`. 
and in case OpenRouter model expects `reasoning` in the result.

Below are code 297-309 from master branch
```
if choices and hasattr(choices[0].message, "reasoning_content"):
    rtn.generations[0].message.additional_kwargs["reasoning_content"] = choices[
        0
    ].message.reasoning_content
# Handle use via OpenRouter
elif choices and hasattr(choices[0].message, "model_extra"):
    model_extra = choices[0].message.model_extra
    if isinstance(model_extra, dict) and (
        reasoning := model_extra.get("reasoning")
    ):
        rtn.generations[0].message.additional_kwargs["reasoning_content"] = (
            reasoning
        )
```
I can remove the `message.additional_kwargs["reasoning"] = reasoning` and only keep it in `message.additional_kwargs["reasoning_content"]`
